%22Pick+a+Bale+O'+Cotton%22%22|date=1 August 2014|publisher=Backbeat Books|isbn=978-1-61713-608-5|pages=23\u2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Johnny Cash]] released his version as a [[single (music)|single]] by [[Columbia Records]] (Columbia 4-42512, with \"[[Bonanza (song)|Bonanza!]]\" on the opposite side)<ref name=\"Banister2014\" /><ref name=\"Turner2005\">{{cite book|author=Steve Turner|title=The Man Called CASH: The Life, Love and Faith of an American Legend|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6qaANnvGwGkC&pg=PT246&q=%22Bonanza%22+%22Pick+A+Bale+O'+Cotton%22+%2242512%22|date=2005-10-30|publisher=Thomas Nelson|isbn=978-1-4185-7809-1|pages=246\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Smith1999\">{{cite book|author=John L. Smith|title=Another Song to Sing: The Recorded Repertoire of Johnny Cash|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vysKAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Bonanza%22|date=1 January 1999|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-3629-7}}<br />{{cite book|author=John L. Smith|title=Another Song to Sing: The Recorded Repertoire of Johnny Cash|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vysKAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Pick+A+Bale+O'+Cotton%22|date=1 January 1999|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-3629-7}}</ref> in July<ref name=\"Lewry2001\">{{cite book|author=Peter Lewry|title=I've Been Everywhere: A Johnny Cash Chronicle|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ocQK9YBdRhkC&q=%22Bonanza%22+%22Pick+A+Bale+O'+Cotton%22+%2242512%22|year=2001|publisher=Helter Skelter|isbn=978-1-900924-22-1|quote=<br>July<br>\"Bonanza\"/\"Pick a Bale O' Cotton\" (Columbia 4-42512) released.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Johnny Cash Record Catalog|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9ihbEBcJEx4C&pg=PA7&dq=%224-42512%22|year=1994|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-29506-5|pages=21\u2013}}</ref> or August 1962.<ref name=\"Turner2005\" />\n\nThe ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine evaluated the single upon its release as having a \"moderate sales potential\".<ref name=\"Billboard 11 August 1962\" />\n\n== Background ==\n{{quote|\n\u201cPick a Bale O'Cotton\u201d is a simple, repetitious song that Cash wrote on the subject of cotton. The carefree lyric \u201cJump down, turn around, pick a bale o' cotton,\u201d tries to put a positive spin on the grueling, merciless work of the cotton farmer. It might have been sung out in the fields as the cotton was being gathered to help alleviate the backbreaking boredom that would set in daily. The song was not released at the time.{{when?|date=April 2020}}|source=John M. Alexander. ''The Man in Song: A Discographic Biography of Johnny Cash''<ref name=\"Alexander2018 (page 74)\">{{cite book|author=John M. Alexander|title=The Man in Song: A Discographic Biography of Johnny Cash|url=https://books.google.ru/books?id=CJlHDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA9&dq=%22Pick+a+Bale+O'Cotton%22|date=16 April 2018|publisher=University of Arkansas Press|isbn=978-1-61075-628-0|pages=41\u2013}}</ref>}}\n\n== Track listing ==\n'''Johnny Cash version'''\n{{Track listing\n| headline      = 7\" single {{nobold|(Columbia 42512, 1962)<ref name=\"Billboard 11 August 1962\" />}}\n| extra_column  = \n| total_length  = \n\n| all_writing   = \n| all_lyrics    = \n| all_music     = \n\n| title_width   = \n| writing_width = \n| music_width   = \n| lyrics_width  =  \n| extra_width   = \n\n| title1        = [[Pick a Bale o' Cotton]]\n| note1         = \n| writer1       = [[Johnny Cash]]\n| lyrics1       = \n| music1        = \n| extra1        = \n| length1       = 1:56\n\n| title2        = Bonanza!\n| note2         = \n| writer2       = [[Livingston & Evans|Jay Livingston \u2013 Raymond Evans]]\n| lyrics2       = \n| music2        = \n| extra2        = \n| length2       = 2:24\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Johnny Cash \u2013 vocal, guitar\n* [[Joe Hancock]] \u2013 banjo\n* [[Marshal Grant]] \u2013 bass\n* [[W. S. Holland]] \u2013 drums\n* [[Luther Perkins]] \u2013 electric guitar\n* [[Bill Pursell]] \u2013 piano<ref name=\"Smith1999\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Johnny Cash}